OL,6,FSeales pleaded guilty to two counts of
OL,7,Ffalse imprisonment and one count of
OL,8,Fblackmail at an earlier hearing.
OL,10,FHe was said to have secured the
OL,11,Fpremises off Fowler Street, where
OL,12,Fvictims were "abused and assaulted".
OL,14,FNewcastle Crown Court heard the 38-
OL,15,Fyear-old was present the entire time
OL,16,Fand was said to have come up with a
OL,17,Fsolution that victims could leave if
OL,18,Fthey paid #20,000 in two days.
